- Oh, shh.

15:03.336 --> 15:05.503
- Well, lucky us.
- Andrew Wallace, hi.

15:05.503 --> 15:07.420
- Nice to meet you.
- Oh, I'm so sorry. Andrew.

15:07.420 --> 15:11.044
- This is Andrew.
- You must be enjoying
that magnifying glass.

15:11.044 --> 15:12.961
You win some,
you lose some.

15:12.961 --> 15:15.836
- Yeah.
- It's a charming place
you have here.

15:15.836 --> 15:17.336
Thank you, thank you.

15:17.336 --> 15:18.836
And I'll introduce you
to the artist.

15:18.836 --> 15:23.670
I'm sure she would love
to hear any pearls of wisdom

15:23.670 --> 15:25.420
that you would care
to share with her.

15:25.420 --> 15:27.753
- Certainly. I'll--
I'll take a look around.
- Okay.

15:29.170 --> 15:30.753
"Pearls of wisdom"?
Good Lord.

15:30.753 --> 15:32.753
Do you ever just hate
the sound of your own voice?

15:32.753 --> 15:35.003
I can't say
that I do, actually.

15:35.003 --> 15:37.420
Oh. Well, then I guess
it's just me.

15:37.420 --> 15:39.753
Well, it's the belle
of the ball.

15:39.753 --> 15:42.211
- Hey, hey, you two. Hi.
- Hi.

15:42.211 --> 15:44.044
- Good to see you again.

15:44.044 --> 15:45.044
Nice to see you as well.

15:45.044 --> 15:46.753
And might I add,
clothes on,

15:46.753 --> 15:48.919
- zipper up, good look.
- Yes.

15:48.919 --> 15:51.420
This is
my girlfriend, Jackie.

15:51.420 --> 15:53.044
- Hi. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

15:53.044 --> 15:55.836
Congratulations, Frances.
The work is stunning.

15:55.836 --> 15:57.420
Oh, thank you, thank you.

15:57.420 --> 16:00.128
It's been-- it's been
a stressful couple of weeks.

16:00.128 --> 16:02.587
- I mean, you know.
- And you have done great...

16:02.587 --> 16:04.878
- Thank you.
You've been a...
- ...dealing with it.

