without your visor.

19:19.003 --> 19:22.503
- Well, this is
my best friend's gallery.

19:22.503 --> 19:23.753
- Oh.

19:23.753 --> 19:25.753
I was having dinner
two doors down

19:25.753 --> 19:28.878
and saw the free wine
was happening, so...

19:28.878 --> 19:31.086
Hey, they were out
of the shrimp, so...

19:31.086 --> 19:34.545
Melinda, this is Dallas
from tennis that I was
telling you about.

19:34.545 --> 19:36.044
Oh, yes.
Hi.

19:36.044 --> 19:37.587
- I'm good, good.

19:37.587 --> 19:39.712
How do you two
know each other?

19:39.712 --> 19:41.462
- Well...
- Uh, funny story.

19:41.462 --> 19:43.462
Melinda is
my soon-to-be ex-wife.

19:43.462 --> 19:44.628
Ooh, I like that.

19:44.628 --> 19:47.295
- I'm gonna steal that.

19:47.295 --> 19:50.128
- The-- the red tape
from our divorce

19:50.128 --> 19:52.295
is literally lasting longer
than the actual marriage.

19:52.295 --> 19:56.295
Yeah, let's just say
we work better as friends.

19:59.420 --> 20:01.003
Well, I'm gonna grab
another drink.

20:01.003 --> 20:03.086
- I'm good.

20:03.086 --> 20:05.295
- I'm good, thank you.
- Okay.

20:09.628 --> 20:11.794
- That looks like
a good drink.
- Oh, it is.

20:11.794 --> 20:13.545
I would have
ordered you one,

20:13.545 --> 20:17.253
except I thought
you'd wanna represent
your own drink choice.

20:17.253 --> 20:18.670
So that's how
it's gonna be?

20:20.003 --> 20:21.295
It's not just
that I'm old enough

20:21.295 --> 20:22.919
to be your mother...

20:22.919 --> 20:24.503
- No, you're not.
- No, you're right, I'm not.

20:24.503 --> 20:27.253
That was a test,
but, um...

20:27.253 --> 20:30.170
I'm a therapist
who treats a lot of people

20:30.170 --> 20:33.295
who are separated
and really conflicted.

20:33.295 --> 20:35.919
It's because
people like me and Melinda
who aren't conflicted

20:35.919 --> 20:37.628
don't go into therapy.

20:37.628 --> 20:40.587
Look, I know it's weird
that we're still friends,

20:40.587 --> 20:43.003
but it's completely
platonic.

20:43.003 --> 20:47.961
So, what I'm hearing
is you've never been
in therapy.

21:04.961 --> 21:08.211
Yeah.
You're obviously upset.

21:08.211 --> 21:10.128
So, what, you're just--
you're gonna fester

21:10.128 --> 21:11.878
for some period of time

21:11.878 --> 21:14.794
and then a week from now
bite my head off,

21:14.794 --> 21:17.044
and all of it because
I wanna get a lawyer.

21:17.044 --> 21:19.044
Dude, I will bite
your head off right now.

21:19.044 --> 21:20.628
I don't care
that you want a lawyer.

21:20.628 --> 21:22.211
Hire a whole team.
Go nuts.

21:22.211 --> 21:23.836
Well, what is
your fucking problem?

21:23.836 --> 21:25.420
You're the one
with a problem.

21:25.420 --> 21:28.378
You're picking a fight,
and none of this
is about me.

21:28.378 --> 21:29.462
It's about Frances.

21:29.462 --> 21:31.044
So, why don't you call me

21:31.044 --> 21:32.919
when you wanna
fight with me?

21:44.878 --> 21:46.919
- Hey.
- Hey.

21:50.587 --> 21:52.628
Why don't we call it
a night and go celebrate
at your place?

21:52.628 --> 21:54.128
Robert's got the kids
tonight, right?

21:54.128 --> 21:55.628
Uh, no.

21:55.628 --> 21:58.253
I mean, um,
they're spending
the night

21:58.253 --> 22:02.211
at a friend's house,
but... you go.

22:02.211 --> 22:03.670
You go.
Save yourself.

22:03.670 --> 22:06.503
I'll, um-- we'll check in
tomorrow, okay?

22:06.503 --> 22:09.086
Uh, what's going on?
Did I do something wrong?

22:09.086 --> 22:11.794
No, that's not--
not it.

22:13.211 --> 22:17.086
Uh, I'm just not sure
that, um...

22:18.295 --> 22:20.878
that this
is such a good idea.

22:20.878 --> 22:24.628
Oh. Well,
there's a curveball.

22:24.628 --> 22:25.753
Can I ask why?

22:25.753 --> 22:28.545
Well-- and I--
this is silly, I know,

22:28.545 --> 22:30.462
but earlier tonight,
somebody asked me out,

22:30.462 --> 22:32.587
and I'll be honest,
I was tempted.

22:32.587 --> 22:34.128
And I know that
we're not serious

22:34.128 --> 22:39.086
or even exclusive, but I--
I felt guilty, which...

22:40.170 --> 22:42.170
you know,
I know it's crazy.

22:42.170 --> 22:44.587
I get it.
I never should've told you
about my ex's affair.

22:44.587 --> 22:47.336
No. No, I-- I--

22:47.336 --> 22:50.545
really, I appreciated
your honesty.

22:50.545 --> 22:52.211
What I couldn't admit
is that

22:52.211 --> 22:55.794
I was actually
the unfaithful one
in my marriage.

22:57.503 --> 22:59.836
I'm not proud.

22:59.836 --> 23:01.295
Well, you lied to me
about that.

23:01.295 --> 23:05.378
Well, yes, I--
I guess yes.

23:05.378 --> 23:08.420
It-- it was a lie
by omission.

23:08.420 --> 23:10.670
No, it was a lie.
You lied.

23:10.670 --> 23:12.003
And you cheated,
apparently.

23:12.003 --> 23:13.336
I'm-- I'm trying
to be honest.

23:13.336 --> 23:14.878
I didn't even have
to bring this up.

23:14.878 --> 23:17.545
Okay. Mm-hmm.

23:17.545 --> 23:19.420
Listen, maybe this is
for the best.

23:19.420 --> 23:21.462
I mean,
you said it yourself
the night we met.

23:21.462 --> 23:24.420
- It's too soon for me
to be getting involved.
- Yeah, no, I remember.

23:24.420 --> 23:27.170
I think my exact words were
you were a walking disaster,

23:27.170 --> 23:29.420
so maybe I should take
comfort in the fact

23:29.420 --> 23:30.670
that my instincts
were right.

23:30.670 --> 23:32.545
You have every right
to be mad, but you--

23:32.545 --> 23:35.044
- you don't have
to, like, attack--

23:35.044 --> 23:37.670
Thanks, Frances.
Thanks, that's really
generous of you.

23:37.670 --> 23:39.295
Wow.

23:42.670 --> 23:44.961
Wow, uh...

23:44.961 --> 23:47.670
I don't really know
how else to say this,

23:47.670 --> 23:50.211
but you're
the walking disaster,
not me.

23:50.211 --> 23:52.878
You got
the walking part right.

24:44.961 --> 24:47.794
- Frances.
Hey.

24:47.794 --> 24:49.587
Oh, I'm so glad
you thought to do this.

24:49.587 --> 24:52.587
- We have to celebrate.

24:54.670 --> 24:57.878
Can we get, um--
can we get two glasses
of champagne, please?

24:57.878 --> 24:59.587
- Sure.
- Thank you.

24:59.587 --> 25:02.295
I don't know about you,
I'm not typically
a day drinker.

25:02.295 --> 25:03.919
However, I think
we've earned it.

25:03.919 --> 25:07.128
- We have.
- Hi!

25:14.836 --> 25:16.712
Hey.

25:16.712 --> 25:18.919
What are you doing?

25:18.919 --> 25:20.919
I'm burying
this fucking raccoon.

25:20.919 --> 25:23.836
Been stinking up my truck
for the last three days.

25:23.836 --> 25:26.420
I can't do it
at my apartment.

25:26.420 --> 25:28.670
It's a rental.

25:28.670 --> 25:30.670
Probably violate
the health code.

25:35.128 --> 25:37.794
- Get right in there.

25:37.794 --> 25:39.794
That's good.

25:39.794 --> 25:41.462
I gotta say...

25:43.794 --> 25:46.878
no one has ever buried
a dead body for me before.

25:48.295 --> 25:50.503
Yeah, it's a first
for me, too.

25:56.128 --> 25:57.753
- Frances: Oh, thank you.
- You're welcome.

25:57.753 --> 25:59.170
Here you go, sir.

25:59.170 --> 26:00.503
Oh, no, I wanted
to treat you.

26:00.503 --> 26:02.753
No, don't be silly.
I'm very happy to.

26:02.753 --> 26:04.878
- Okay, well, thank you.
- You're very welcome.

26:06.170 --> 26:09.211
Actually...
there's one more thing.

26:09.211 --> 26:11.170
Oh, okay.

26:11.170 --> 26:13.670
God, I just got nervous.

26:13.670 --> 26:14.670
No, don't be.

26:14.670 --> 26:16.628
Okay, so, Skip Zakarian

26:16.628 --> 26:18.295
has offered me--
you know Skip Zakarian?

26:18.295 --> 26:20.794
- Of course.
- He wants to rep me.

26:20.794 --> 26:22.753
Like, exclusively.

26:22.753 --> 26:24.503
Starting with
a big-ass SoHo show

26:24.503 --> 26:27.044
